    "content": "A — Yes. The experts review for philosophical accuracy and terminological precision, but none of us are specifically tasked with evaluating whether the English prose reads well as continuous, publishable text. Philosophical translation can easily produce sentences that are technically correct but stilted, overly parenthetical, or inconsistent in register across passages. An Editor agent focused on prose quality, flow, and cross-essay stylistic coherence would catch issues that fall outside our domain expertise — awkward phrasing, unnecessary repetition, tonal shifts, paragraph-level readability — and would free the experts to focus on what we do best. This is especially important for a work like this one, where the original Chinese has a distinctive authorial voice that the translation should preserve as natural English rather than as translationese."
